</li>
<li>
<p><code>DROP_START</code>: a drop operation onto the window has started.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>DROP_FINISHED</code>: the drop operation initiated by the window has completed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>CLIENT_EVENT</code>: a message has been received from another application.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>VISIBILITY_NOTIFY</code>: the window visibility status has changed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>SCROLL</code>: the scroll wheel was turned</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>WINDOW_STATE</code>: the state of a window has changed. See
  <a href="http://valadoc.org/#!api=gdk-3.0/Gdk.WindowState"><code>Gdk.WindowState</code></a> for
  the possible window states</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>SETTING</code>: a setting has been modified.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>OWNER_CHANGE</code>: the owner of a selection has changed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>GRAB_BROKEN</code>: a pointer or keyboard grab was broken.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><code>DAMAGE</code>: the content of the window has been changed.</p>
</li>
<li>
